reviews.review: Everything you could ask for in a trilogy finale. JJ did the fanbase right.

I'll always be a Star Wars fan no matter what the community says or does. This movie was incredible to me, I couldn't stop smiling for 10 minutes after leaving the Cinema as well as my sister. JJ, you wrapped this up well. I'm grateful for all my Star Wars memories. My childhood was amazing thanks to it and I know it will be to others for generations to come. May the force be with you, always.

The best of the three sequel movies. 
After the mess that was episode 8 I didnt really expect much,
but they really tied up some of the weird plot.
The jokes were good, the score was great and there were lots of references to other SW media. I'd say its worth watching!
A lame and desperate effort to save an already dead franchise
Such a satisfying conclusion to the saga. It fixed all the main issues of The Last Jedi and was filled with spectacular visuals and exciting twists!
This film does not deserve the ~50% rating this is awesome and definitely recommend it.

The first 30 minutes or so are catastrophic, whiplash-inducing editing jumping from planet to planet and scene to scene with no concept of pacing.

The middle, once the film decides to settle down a bit is perfectly good. The interactions between kylo and Rey are well done and continue to impress.

The end showcases JJ Abrams desire to just make things bigger and flashier with no real thought about making sense or being satisfying, but the ending somewhat lands with the arc coming to a relatively satisfying conclusion.

Overall, worth a watch but certainly in the rankings for one of the worse star wars movies made.

It was visually very  nice, good movie. Story might have been a little too fast at the start. Some characters felt underused, however, if you were to use them all the movie might be too long. So I get it. 

If you're looking for the next deep expansive emotional movie, might want to skip it. This is Star Wars, a tale of good vs evil in space. With Lasers! and Lightsabers! and Aliens. It's a fun movie. Not to be watched Solo (mind the pun), but in the sequence it was made. Watch the others first.

I am a hater of the new star wars.  However JJ was handed a huge turd.  A massive pile of poo.  And to be fair he has polished this turd to the point it IS a watchable movie. I think it is better than The last Jedi and the force awakens.  It has massive problems.  But considering the mess Rian Johnson left on the floor JJ was never going to be able to really fix it.  However he did not a bad job.  A turd but a well dressed up polished and frankly enjoyable one.

The CGI was good, and the fan-service wasn't excessive and it didn't feel forced most of the time. But the camera angles and lightsaber fights are really boring and uninspired, I like the characters conclusions and the characters additions are nice, but some of them are really boring and uninteresting,overall this is a solid movie and a nice series conclusion.
